	<!-- FORGE / FINERY Shear Steel -->		
	<RecipeDef>
		<defName>MakeForgeWeldedSteel_BlisterSteel_Finery</defName>
		<label>Forge Shear Steel (x30)</label>
		<description>Blister steel has an uneven distribution of carbon, in other words, it's nonhomogenous. Beat it on an anvil until it (mostly) is. This is called "shear steel", because it can hold an sharp edge if you wanted to make some shears, but it's still a forge-welded steel. Produced 20 Forge-Welded Steel.</description>
		<jobString>Forging-welding steel form blister steel. Produces 30.</jobString>
